APPy (
https://github.com/habanero-lab/APPy
) could be a good fit for your case, if you need to parallelize a simple for loop on the GPU. It supports torch gpu and cupy tensors as inputs. The APPy parallelized version of 
select_next
 based on your pytorch code looks like this:


@appy.jit
def select_next_appy(X, gains, current_values, mask, N):
    #pragma parallel for
    for idx in range(X.shape[0]):
        if mask[idx] != 1:            
            a = torch.maximum(X[idx, :N], current_values[:N])            
            gains[idx] = torch.sum(a - current_values[:N])
    return torch.argmax(gains)



